<div class="worksheet-content">
<h1>ğŸ›ï¸ Government & Governance Design Template</h1>
<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Design the decision-making and leadership structures for your society</p>

<div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #eff6ff, #dbeafe); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; margin: 1.5rem 0; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-info);">
<h3>What is Governance?</h3>
<p>Governance is how decisions are made in a society. Good governance ensures:</p>
<ul>
<li>Fair and transparent decision-making</li>
<li>Everyone has a voice (or representation)</li>
<li>Power is balanced and accountable</li>
<li>Leaders serve the people, not themselves</li>
<li>Decisions benefit the common good</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2>Part 1: Core Governance Principles</h2>

<div style="background: white; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd; margin: 1rem 0;">
<p><strong>What principles will guide decision-making in your society?</strong></p>

<table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0;">
<thead>
<tr style="background: var(--color-pounamu); color: white;">
<th style="padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Governance Principle</th>
<th style="padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #ddd;">How It Works in Your Society</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><strong>Transparency</strong><br><small>Open decision-making</small></td>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><strong>Accountability</strong><br><small>Leaders answer to people</small></td>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><strong>Participation</strong><br><small>People have voice</small></td>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><strong>Equity</strong><br><small>Fair treatment for all</small></td>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>

<h2>Part 2: Leadership Structure</h2>

<div style="background: white; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd; margin: 1rem 0;">
<p><strong>Who makes decisions? Choose or design your own system:</strong></p>

<div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin: 1rem 0;">
<div style="padding: 1rem; background: rgba(27, 67, 50, 0.05); border-radius: 6px; border: 2px solid transparent;">
<label style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start;">
<input type="radio" name="gov_type" style="margin-right: 0.5rem; margin-top: 0.25rem;">
<div>
<strong>Direct Democracy</strong>
<p style="font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 0.5rem 0;">All citizens vote on all decisions</p>
<small>Pros: Maximum participation | Cons: Slow, impractical for large populations</small>
</div>
</label>
</div>

<div style="padding: 1rem; background: rgba(27, 67, 50, 0.05); border-radius: 6px;">
<label style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start;">
<input type="radio" name="gov_type" style="margin-right: 0.5rem; margin-top: 0.25rem;">
<div>
<strong>Representative Democracy</strong>
<p style="font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 0.5rem 0;">Elected representatives make decisions</p>
<small>Pros: Practical, balanced | Cons: Can disconnect from people</small>
</div>
</label>
</div>

<div style="padding: 1rem; background: rgba(27, 67, 50, 0.05); border-radius: 6px;">
<label style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start;">
<input type="radio" name="gov_type" style="margin-right: 0.5rem; margin-top: 0.25rem;">
<div>
<strong>Council of Elders</strong>
<p style="font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 0.5rem 0;">Wisdom-based leadership</p>
<small>Pros: Experience, long-term thinking | Cons: May lack youth perspective</small>
</div>
</label>
</div>

<div style="padding: 1rem; background: rgba(27, 67, 50, 0.05); border-radius: 6px;">
<label style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start;">
<input type="radio" name="gov_type" style="margin-right: 0.5rem; margin-top: 0.25rem;">
<div>
<strong>Consensus Model</strong>
<p style="font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 0.5rem 0;">Decisions require broad agreement</p>
<small>Inspired by hui/wÄnanga | Pros: Unity | Cons: Time-consuming</small>
</div>
</label>
</div>

<div style="padding: 1rem; background: rgba(27, 67, 50, 0.05); border-radius: 6px;">
<label style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start;">
<input type="radio" name="gov_type" style="margin-right: 0.5rem; margin-top: 0.25rem;">
<div>
<strong>Mixed/Hybrid System</strong>
<p style="font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 0.5rem 0;">Combine multiple approaches</p>
<small>Pros: Flexibility | Design your own unique system!</small>
</div>
</label>
</div>
</div>

<h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Describe Your Leadership Structure:</h3>
<textarea style="width: 100%; min-height: 120px; padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 4px; font-family: inherit;" placeholder="Who are the leaders? How are they chosen? What are their powers and limits? How long do they serve?"></textarea>
</div>

<h2>Part 3: Decision-Making Process</h2>

<div style="background: white; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd; margin: 1rem 0;">
<p><strong>Walk us through how a major decision gets made:</strong></p>

<div style="background: var(--color-gray-50); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 6px; margin: 1rem 0;">
<h4>Step 1: Proposal</h4>
<p><em>Who can propose new laws or policies?</em></p>
<textarea style="width: 100%; min-height: 60px; padding: 0.5rem; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 4px; font-family: inherit;"></textarea>
</div>

<div style="background: var(--color-gray-50); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 6px; margin: 1rem 0;">
<h4>Step 2: Discussion</h4>
<p><em>How is the proposal debated and examined?</em></p>
<textarea style="width: 100%; min-height: 60px; padding: 0.5rem; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 4px; font-family: inherit;"></textarea>
</div>

<div style="background: var(--color-gray-50); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 6px; margin: 1rem 0;">
<h4>Step 3: Decision</h4>
<p><em>How is the final decision made? Who votes? What majority is needed?</em></p>
<textarea style="width: 100%; min-height: 60px; padding: 0.5rem; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 4px; font-family: inherit;"></textarea>
</div>

<div style="background: var(--color-gray-50); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 6px; margin: 1rem 0;">
<h4>Step 4: Implementation</h4>
<p><em>How is the decision put into action? Who enforces it?</em></p>
<textarea style="width: 100%; min-height: 60px; padding: 0.5rem; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 4px; font-family: inherit;"></textarea>
</div>

<div style="background: var(--color-gray-50); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 6px; margin: 1rem 0;">
<h4>Step 5: Review</h4>
<p><em>How do you know if the decision is working? Can it be changed?</em></p>
<textarea style="width: 100%; min-height: 60px; padding: 0.5rem; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 4px; font-family: inherit;"></textarea>
</div>
</div>

<h2>Part 4: Checks & Balances</h2>

<div style="background: white; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd; margin: 1rem 0;">
<p><strong>How do you prevent abuse of power?</strong></p>

<table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0;">
<thead>
<tr style="background: var(--color-info); color: white;">
<th style="padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Branch/Body</th>
<th style="padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Powers</th>
<th style="padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Checks On It</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Executive/Leadership</td>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"></td>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Legislature/Law-makers</td>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"></td>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Judiciary/Courts</td>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"></td>
<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid #ddd;"></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>

<h2>Part 5: Cultural Integration</h2>

<div style="background: rgba(27, 67, 50, 0.1); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-pounamu); margin: 1rem 0;">
<p><strong>How does your governance reflect MÄori democratic traditions?</strong></p>
<p><em>Consider: hui (consensus gathering), wÄnanga (knowledge sharing), tikanga (protocols), mana (authority through service)</em></p>
